Time-dependent model¶

In [ ]:
function sir_TB(du, u, params, t)
    (S, L, Ti, Tn, R, tTB) = u
    (, T, p, v, f, q, , c, AveI, b, D, D, ) = params
     = 1/
     = AveI*/
    

    @inbounds begin
         = /((1+b*D*t)^(1/b))
        T = T/(1+ D*t)
        
        du[1] =  - *Ti*S - *S # dX/dt
        du[2] =  (1-p)**Ti*S - (v + )*L # dL/dt
        du[3] = p*f**Ti*S + q*v*L + *R - ( + T + c)*Ti # dTi/dt
        du[4] = p*(1-f)**Ti*S + (1-q)*v*L + *R - ( + T + c)*Tn # dTn/dt
        du[5] = c*(Ti + Tn) - (2* + )*R # dR/dt

        du[6] = p**Ti*S + v*L + 2**R

    end
    nothing
end;
In [ ]:
@model function bayes_TB(infected, u0)
    #calculate number of timepoints
    l = length(infected)

     = 3e6
    T = 0.015

    # priors
     ~ Uniform(60, 80)
    
    p ~ TriangularDist(0, 0.3, 0.05)
    v ~ Uniform(0.00256, 0.00527)
    f ~ TriangularDist(0.5, 0.85, 0.7)
    q ~ TriangularDist(0.5, 1, 0.85)
     ~ TriangularDist(0, 0.015, 0.005)
    c ~ TriangularDist(0.021, 0.086, 0.058)
    AveI ~ TriangularDist(0, 13, 1)
    
    b ~ Uniform(0, 1)
    D ~ TruncatedNormal(0.5, 2, 1e-4, 10)
    D ~ TruncatedNormal(0.5, 2, 1e-4, 10)

     ~ truncated(Exponential(5), 0, 1e5)
     = 1.0 / 

    
    #ODE Stuff
    
    params = [, T, p, v, f, q, , c, AveI, b, D, D, ]
 
    tspan = (1.0, float(l))
    prob = ODEProblem(sir_TB,
            u0,
            tspan,
            params)
    sol = solve(prob,
                Tsit5(), # similar to Dormand-Prince RK45 in Stan but 20% faster
                saveat=1.0)
    new_infected = Array(sol)[6, :] 
    sol = insert!(diff(new_infected), 1, new_infected[1])
    sol = max.(1e-4, sol) # numerical issues arose

    #likelihood
    infected ~ arraydist(LazyArray(@~ NegativeBinomial2.(sol, )))

end;

In [ ]:
function sir_solve(param, u0, infected)
    prob = ODEProblem(sir_TB, u0, (1.0, float(length(infected))), param)
    sol = solve(prob,
            Tsit5(), # similar to Dormand-Prince RK45 in Stan but 20% faster
            saveat=1.0)
    new_infected = Array(sol)[6, :] 
    sol = insert!(diff(new_infected), 1, new_infected[1])

    sol
end

function sir_pred_all(chain, fixed_params, u0, infected)
    params = DataFrame(chain)
    , T = fixed_params
    #sols = []
    for i in 1:nrow(params)
        param_iter = params[i,:]
        _, _, , p, v, f, q, , c, AveI, b, D, D = param_iter
        
        param = [, T,   p, v, f, q, , c, AveI, b, D, D, ]
        
        sol = sir_solve(param, u0, infected)
        
        #push!(sols, copy(sol))
        if i == 1
            global sols = DataFrame(x = sol)
        else
            sols = hcat(sols, sol, makeunique=true)
        end
    end
    
    sols
end

function sir_TB2(du, u, params, t)
    (S, L, Ti, Tn, R, tTB) = u
    (, , p, v, f, q, , T, c, AveI) = params
     = 1/
     = AveI*/

        du[4] = p*(1-f)**Ti*S + (1-q)*v*L + *R - ( + T + c)*Tn # dTn/dt
        du[5] = c*(Ti + Tn) - (2* + )*R # dR/dt

    end

    #calculate number of timepoints
    l = length(infected)

     = 3e6
    T = 0.015

    # priors 
     ~ Uniform(60, 80) 
    p ~ TriangularDist(0, 0.3, 0.05)
    v ~ Uniform(0.00256, 0.00527)
    f ~ TriangularDist(0.5, 0.85, 0.7)
    q ~ TriangularDist(0.5, 1, 0.85)
     ~ TriangularDist(0, 0.015, 0.005)
    c ~ TriangularDist(0.021, 0.086, 0.058)

     ~ truncated(Exponential(5), 0, 1e5)
     = 1.0 /

    param = [, , p, v, f, q, , T, c, AveI]
    tspan = (1.0, float(l))
    prob = ODEProblem(sir_TB2,
            u0,
            tspan,
            param)
    sol = solve(prob,
                Tsit5(), # similar to Dormand-Prince RK45 in Stan but 20% faster
                saveat=1.0)
    new_infected = Array(sol)[6, :] 
    sol = insert!(diff(new_infected), 1, new_infected[1])
    sol = max.(1e-4, sol) # numerical issues arose

    #likelihood
    infected ~ arraydist(LazyArray(@~ NegativeBinomial2.(sol, )))

     = 1/
     = AveI*/
    

    Rf = (**)/( + T + c) * p * f
    Rs = (**)/( + T + c) * (q*(1-p)*v/(v+))
    Rr = (**)/(( + T + c)^2 - (2**c)/(2* + )) * (p + (1.0- p)*v/(v+)) * (*c/(2* + ))
    R0 = Rf + Rs + Rr

    return R0
end;

In [ ]:
function sir_solve2(param, u0, infected)
    prob = ODEProblem(sir_TB2, u0, (1.0, float(length(infected))), param)
    sol = solve(prob,
            Tsit5(), # similar to Dormand-Prince RK45 in Stan but 20% faster
            saveat=1.0)
    new_infected = Array(sol)[6, :] 
    sol = insert!(diff(new_infected), 1, new_infected[1])

    sol
end

function sir_pred_all2(chain, fixed_params, u0, infected)
    params = DataFrame(chain)
    , T = fixed_params
    #sols = []
    for i in 1:nrow(params)
        param_iter = params[i,:]
        _, _, , p, v, f, q, , c, AveI, _ = param_iter
        
        param = [, , p, v, f, q, , T, c, AveI]
        
        sol = sir_solve2(param, u0, infected)
        
        #push!(sols, copy(sol))
        if i == 1
            global sols = DataFrame(x = sol)
        else
            sols = hcat(sols, sol, makeunique=true)
        end
    end
    
    sols
end
